The following months, however, showed that the Bush strategy, based on military recommendations, was the only possible and very successful one to the extent that the news about Iraq no longer speaks at all.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, for objectively he left a much more appreciative starting point for his successor than was to be expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will be repeated.
The military again asked him to increase the contingent of troops, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghanistan operation General Stanley McCristal, who strongly criticized the timid gunmen in the White House even in spite of the subordination habits.
