If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions do not affect Iranians, the United States will have a very difficult question as to whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question must be answered during the period when America is moving to the winning withdrawal from Afghanistan after Obama.
But any solution will also mean a dramatic turn of the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that three years remain until the presidential election, and so there is still enough time for him to resort to another strategy that would turn out to be a total failure.
