Manager revolution or the end of the Strategic Early Enlightenment?
If nothing changes in the leadership of the great French companies, our struggle for the development of economic intelligence has been in vain ...
For over a decade, the attitude of managing large companies in terms of its employees, said the position of the companies vis-à-vis the consumer before the marketing revolution: It is determined for the personnel to join "values" to impose the best, as it used to be on the consumer products designed by the technicians in the factory.
