Audatex offers this offer not in Spain, but in the United States.
When looking at the products Audatex offers, you can easily get an overview of the kind of support it gives to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, the star of which is AudaPlus, a standard solution for investigating accidents for the reviewers.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
Apart from the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid according to the intended use, i.e. for each expert report.
The most expensive is for customers who rarely use it, a maximum of ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
On the other hand, every insurance company that makes thousands of reports negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can completely identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran from the assembly line, using the chassis number alone.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle discs, and AudaSubastas is an open service to the specialist market on the Internet, with which one can offer for vehicles that have been declared total damage.
Your statistics service is very useful in identifying trends, conducting geodemographic analyses or obtaining information about the differences by brand and model.
It can be used, for example, to examine how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop due to breakdowns or how many of them were involved in a serious accident in a certain period of time.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of computer tools.
It distributes among other Gt Estimate, which is also intended for reviewers and delivers in the same way digital images, access to parts or prices and official working hours of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa Group, founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damage, breakdowns or maintenance of vehicles.
The GT expert opinion guide is a reference product on the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 reviewers and 53 insurance companies.
Their business volume has increased by 20% annually over the last three years and in 2008 sales amounted to 10.8 million euros.
At the beginning of last year, they began to go on the international market with the opening of an office in Paris.
