On the other hand, cars with historical value may be re-registered, even if they have been cancelled after difficult administrative procedures.
Estimation of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives an estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of an estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course you need a computer with internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified on the basis of the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the working hours, surcharges or discounts, and after that he can print out the estimate and pass it on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for evaluation such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the working time targeted at the workshop does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
At the moment, Audatex is working to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that auto mechanics have been waiting for a long time for, for example, to select a door with it and then turn the image completely around to look at the inside.
